 Pendulum.\nAs 1 thought over my position uy\nheart sank with me. It was of no use\nto call for assistance, for I was 150\nfeet in the alr. The wind was shriek\ning and moaning and the noise of the\nmachinery in the pumping station \u2018ar\nbelow would drown any sound 1 could\nmake. To stay in my present situation\nfor any length of time, however, was\nclearly out of the question, for even if\nI could manage to weep from being\nthrown off, my scaffold would soon be\ndashed to pieces and I myself stunned\nor disabled by striking the ciimney.\nAll this time that awful pendulum meo\ntion was going on, with the inevitable\ncrash against the chimney every time\nI swung in. I was now becoming dizzy\nfrom the continual whirling arcund-\u2014\nfirst one way and then another. F.nally\nI grew desperate. I realized that some\nthing must be done if 1 did not wish t\u00ab\nbe hurled down to my death, Nervinz\nmyself for a last effort I lowered rayself\nuntil I hung down, holding with both\nhands to the bottom of the scaffold. In\nthis precarious position, before the\nstage swung in and shook me off, 1\nmanaged to take a turn of the fall\naround my leg, and, letting go the\nscaffold, slid down.\u2014 Wide World Maga\nzine.\n$150,000 RESIDENCE\nFOR DUPONT CIRCLE\nMrs. S. R. Hitt Contracts With\nGeorge A. Fuller Company\nfor New Home\nA contract for the erection of ajloti er\nresidence for Dupont circle has been\ngiven to the George A. Fuller Company,\nand work will be begun at once, Mrs.\n8S. R. Hitt yesterday cabled the Fuller\nCompany to commence the building.\nThe new house is to be situated be\ntween the Patterson and Leiter resi\ndences, and will cost about $150,000.\nFlans for the house were drawn by\nJohn Russell Pope, of New York. The\nmaterials are to be Indiana limestiae\nand brick. and an entirely new ads\nration of English architecture has bedn\nmade in the plans.\nAR\nCONVERSATION\nI'm at a loss what to have my hero\nsay Any\nRak al novei?\u201d\nYes\u201d\n\u201cHav